# v0.1.0

- Bug fixes:
    - scx-adapt does not keep running if sched_ext scheduler crashes anymore (Checks state at: `/sys/kernel/sched_ext/state`)
    - `scx-adapt.lock exists` problem when exited with error
- Added:
    - `add-scheduler`, `remove-scheduler`, `list-schedulers` commands
    - Load schedulers from added schedulers (`add-scheduler`) automatically in .yaml config
- Changed:
    - Program files moved from `/etc/scx-adapt` to `/var/lib/scx-adapt`
    - `check-profile` now reads file from path positional argument (instead of STDIN)
    - **TODO** looks more beautiful

[X] Fix scx-adapt keeps running even if sched_ext scheduler crashes bug (check status of sched_ext: `/sys/kernel/sched_ext/state`)
[X] Fix `scx-adapt.lock exists` problem when exited with error and lock doesn't get deleted.
[X] `add-scheduler`, `remove-scheduler`, `list-schedulers` commands (to *SCHEDULERSFOLDER*).
[X] Load schedulers in *SCHEDULERSFOLDER* automatically in .yaml config (Refer to file in *SCHEDULERSFOLDER* if filepath in yaml is not absolute)
[X] Change `check-profile` to read file from file path.
[X] Move files to `/var/lib/scx-adapt`
[X] Enhance TODO with Markdown 

